ame is also found among Native Americans (mainly Pueblos)."],"variants":[{"name":"Padillo","meanings":["Spanish: altered form of   Padilla  , with the male suffix <i>-o</i> for matching with the sex of the bearer of the surname."]}]},{"name":"Lope","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Late Latin name <i>Lupus</i> ‘wolf’, probably adopted as a calque of the Germanic name   Wolf   ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Garcia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."],"variants":[{"name":"Marsha","meanings":["Phonetic spelling of   Marcia  , associated particularly with the American film star  Marsha Hunt  (  b. 1917 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lope Garcia Padilla was born in 1230, in Sevilla, Andalusia, Spain, his father, Garcia Gutierrez de Padilla, was 39 and his mother, Mrs Garcia Gutierrez De Padilla, was 23. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Lope Garcia Padilla. He died in 1253, in Spain, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1230–1253":"1230–1253","1234–Female":"1234–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1256–1336":"1256–1336","1191–1266":"1191–1266","1208–Female":"1208–Surnud","1336":"1336","1256":"1256","1234":"1234","1266":"1266","1253":"1253","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1208":"1208","1191":"1191","Padilla line":"Padilla, La Guajira, Kolumbia","Seville, Andalucía, Spain":"Sevilla, Andalucía, Hispaania","Spain":"Hispaania"},"fi":{"1230–1253":"1230–1253","1234–Female":"1234–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","125